<h3>Can you tell me more about where you come from, your childhood and your family ? </h3>
<p> «I come from a family with five girls. My mother is from Manawan, my father from Wemo. At the beginning, we were five girls, and my parents got divorced, so today I also have a brother and two other sisters. So we are 8 children. I’m the oldest in my family, so I care a lot for my sisters, I’m very close to them let’s say. I grew up in Wemo and I spent a year in Manawan afterwards, but just a year. Then, I came back to Wemo to finish my secondary school.» </p>
